# /accessibility — Accessibility Audit

## Usage
```
/accessibility [target]
```

## WCAG 2.1 Level AA — Checklist

### 1. Perceivable
- [ ] **Alt text**: All images with descriptive alt (or `alt=""` for decorative)
- [ ] **Color contrast**: Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- [ ] **Resizing**: Content readable at 200% zoom
- [ ] **Don't rely on color alone**: Info conveyed by color has alternative (icon, text)

### 2. Operable
- [ ] **Keyboard navigation**: All interactive elements accessible via Tab/Enter/Space
- [ ] **Visible focus**: Clear focus indicator on all interactive elements
- [ ] **No focus traps**: Tab traverses all elements without getting stuck
- [ ] **Skip links**: Link to skip navigation on complex pages
- [ ] **Touch targets**: Minimum 44x44px on touch devices

### 3. Understandable
- [ ] **Labels**: Every input has associated label (`htmlFor`/`aria-label`/`aria-labelledby`)
- [ ] **Errors**: Error messages identify field and suggest correction
- [ ] **Instructions**: Fields with special format have visible instructions
- [ ] **Language**: `lang` attribute on HTML

### 4. Robust
- [ ] **Semantic HTML**: Correct use of `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`
- [ ] **ARIA roles**: Correct roles when semantic HTML is insufficient
- [ ] **Headings**: Logical hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3, no skipping levels)
- [ ] **Live regions**: `aria-live` for dynamic content (alerts, notifications)

## Correction Patterns

### Icon button (no text)
```jsx
<button aria-label="Close modal">
  <XIcon aria-hidden="true" />
</button>
```

### Input with label
```jsx
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input id="email" type="email" aria-describedby="email-help" />
<span id="email-help">Format: user@domain.com</span>
```

### Informative image
```jsx
<img src="chart.png" alt="Chart showing 30% increase in sales" />
```

### Decorative image
```jsx
<img src="decoration.png" alt="" role="presentation" />
```

## Output Format

